<p>The <code>content</code> tag stores content to the content store for later retrieval with <code>get</code>.</p>

<h2>Basic Content Storage</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'myContent'{close}This is stored content{open}/content{close}
Later: {open}get 'myContent'{close}</pre>
{content 'myContent'}This is stored content{/content}
<p>Later: {get 'myContent'}</p>

<h2>Store HTML Fragment</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'header'{close}
  &lt;div style="background:#333; color:white; padding:10px;"&gt;
    Site Header
  &lt;/div&gt;
{open}/content{close}</pre>
{content 'header'}
<div style="background:#333; color:white; padding:10px;">
  Site Header
</div>
{/content}
<p>Using stored header:</p>
{get 'header'}

<h2>Store Reusable Component</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'divider'{close}&lt;hr style="border:1px dashed #ccc; margin:10px 0;"&gt;{open}/content{close}</pre>
{content 'divider'}<hr style="border:1px dashed #ccc; margin:10px 0;">{/content}
<p>Section 1</p>
{get 'divider'}
<p>Section 2</p>
{get 'divider'}
<p>Section 3</p>

<h2>Store with Variables</h2>
<pre>{open}set version='1.0.0'{close}
{open}content 'footer'{close}Version: {open}$version{close}{open}/content{close}</pre>
{set version='1.0.0'}
{content 'footer'}Version: {$version}{/content}
<p>Footer shows: {get 'footer'}</p>

<h2>Multiple Content Stores</h2>
<pre>{open}content 'a'{close}Content A{open}/content{close}
{open}content 'b'{close}Content B{open}/content{close}
{open}content 'c'{close}Content C{open}/content{close}</pre>
{content 'a'}Content A{/content}
{content 'b'}Content B{/content}
{content 'c'}Content C{/content}
<p>Getting in different order: {get 'c'}, {get 'a'}, {get 'b'}</p>
